                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 137216,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has our opinion this morning in case 07-608, United States versus Hayes."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.669,
                        "stop": 272.688,
                        "byte_start": 137216,
                        "byte_stop": 1197160,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.669,
                                "stop": 14.844,
                                "byte_start": 137216,
                                "byte_stop": 165951,
                                "text": "Federal law has long prohibited the possession of firearms by a convicted felon."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.844,
                                "stop": 25.689,
                                "byte_start": 165951,
                                "byte_stop": 209314,
                                "text": "In 1996, Congress extended this ban to persons convicted of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.689,
                                "stop": 30.404,
                                "byte_start": 209314,
                                "byte_stop": 228122,
                                "text": "The definition of that phrase is the issue in this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.404,
                                "stop": 48.391,
                                "byte_start": 228122,
                                "byte_stop": 300116,
                                "text": "Does it cover a misdemeanor battery whenever the battered victim was in fact the offender\u0027s current or former spouse or other statutorily defined domestic relation notably the offender\u0027s child?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.391,
                                "stop": 63.504,
                                "byte_start": 300116,
                                "byte_stop": 360615,
                                "text": "Or is the gun possession ban triggered only when the predicate misdemeanor identifies as an expressed element of the crime, a domestic relationship between the aggressor and the victim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.504,
                                "stop": 76.28,
                                "byte_start": 360615,
                                "byte_stop": 411711,
                                "text": "We hold that the domestic relationship while that must be established beyond a reasonable doubt need not be a defining element of the predicate events."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.28,
                                "stop": 88.49,
                                "byte_start": 411711,
                                "byte_stop": 460507,
                                "text": "Respondent Randy Hayes was charged with three counts of possessing firearms after having been convicted of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.49,
                                "stop": 100.854,
                                "byte_start": 460507,
                                "byte_stop": 509931,
                                "text": "The indictment identified Hayes\u0027 predicate events as a 1994 conviction for battery in violation of West Virginia law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.854,
                                "stop": 105.437,
                                "byte_start": 509931,
                                "byte_stop": 528321,
                                "text": "The victim of that battery was Hayes\u0027 then wife."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.437,
                                "stop": 115.781,
                                "byte_start": 528321,
                                "byte_stop": 569699,
                                "text": "Hayes sought to dismiss the indictment observing that his West Virginia statute of conviction was a generic battery proscription."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.781,
                                "stop": 130.919,
                                "byte_start": 569699,
                                "byte_stop": 630199,
                                "text": "The firearm ban he asserted applied only to persons convicted of an offense that includes a domestic relationship between the offender and the victim as a defining element."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.919,
                                "stop": 137.966,
                                "byte_start": 630199,
                                "byte_stop": 658411,
                                "text": "The District Court rejected Hayes\u0027 argument, and Hayes entered a conditional guilty plea."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.966,
                                "stop": 145.69,
                                "byte_start": 658411,
                                "byte_stop": 689340,
                                "text": "On appeal, the United States Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit agreed with Hayes and reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.69,
                                "stop": 154.842,
                                "byte_start": 689340,
                                "byte_stop": 725912,
                                "text": "In so holding, the Court split from the nine other Courts of Appeals that have decided the question."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 154.842,
                                "stop": 159.06,
                                "byte_start": 725912,
                                "byte_stop": 742839,
                                "text": "We reverse the Fourth Circuit\u0027s judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.06,
                                "stop": 166.679,
                                "byte_start": 742839,
                                "byte_stop": 773245,
                                "text": "We first explain why the text and context of the governing statute support our reading."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.679,
                                "stop": 170.746,
                                "byte_start": 773245,
                                "byte_stop": 789546,
                                "text": "We next take account of practical considerations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 170.746,
                                "stop": 184.301,
                                "byte_start": 789546,
                                "byte_stop": 843776,
                                "text": "Felon-in-possession laws, Congress recognized, were failing to keep firearms out of the hands of domestic abusers who are often charged with misdemeanors rather than felonies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 184.301,
                                "stop": 194.112,
                                "byte_start": 843776,
                                "byte_stop": 882960,
                                "text": "To close this loophole, Congress extended the federal firearm prohibition to misdemeanor crimes of domestic violence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 194.112,
                                "stop": 204.848,
                                "byte_start": 882960,
                                "byte_stop": 925905,
                                "text": "Excluding from the statutory definition, domestic abusers convicted under generic battery laws would frustrate Congress\u0027 manifest purpose."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 204.848,
                                "stop": 215.182,
                                "byte_start": 925905,
                                "byte_stop": 967283,
                                "text": "As of 1996, only about a third of the states had criminal statutes that specifically proscribe domestic violence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 215.182,
                                "stop": 220.083,
                                "byte_start": 967283,
                                "byte_stop": 986927,
                                "text": "Even today, the number is only modestly higher."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 220.083,
                                "stop": 233.596,
                                "byte_start": 986927,
                                "byte_stop": 1040948,
                                "text": "If the Fourth Circuit were right in its analysis of the controlling legislation, Congress\u0027 enactment would have been a dead letter in the majorly of states from the very moment of its passage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 233.596,
                                "stop": 240.327,
                                "byte_start": 1040948,
                                "byte_stop": 1067907,
                                "text": "We decline to treat the congressional endeavor as in large measure ineffectual."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 240.327,
                                "stop": 260.35,
                                "byte_start": 1067907,
                                "byte_stop": 1147946,
                                "text": "What little there is of legislative history corroborates our ruling, it indicates that Congress sought to apply the firearm ban to all persons convicted of domestic violence offenses whether or not the statutes of conviction happened to contain a domestic relations element."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 260.35,
                                "stop": 265.001,
                                "byte_start": 1147946,
                                "byte_stop": 1166545,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas joins all but Part III of the Court\u0027s opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 265.001,
                                "stop": 272.688,
                                "byte_start": 1166545,
                                "byte_stop": 1197160,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justice Scalia joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
